hints.description: This company connects billions of people worldwide through social media platforms. It offers a range of services including social networking, online advertising, and virtual and augmented reality experiences. Mark Zuckerberg co-founded the company from his Harvard dorm room and it has become a dominant force in the digital advertising landscape.
hints.funFact1: Initially, the company was called "The Facebook" and was exclusively for Harvard University students before expanding to other universities and eventually the general public. It famously rejected a $1 billion buyout offer from Viacom in 2006.
hints.funFact2: The company owns Instagram, WhatsApp, and Oculus, demonstrating a strategy of acquiring popular platforms and integrating them into its ecosystem. Its Reality Labs division is heavily invested in developing the metaverse, a persistent, shared virtual world.
